   <text type="translation">
      <body>
         <pb facs="1870_09_29_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_R_Gaertner_Hakodate_1.tif" n="1"/>
         <p>Hakodate 29th September 1870.<lb/>Messrs. L. Kniffler &amp; Co. Yokohama.<lb/>Since
                my respectful last letter from 16th of this month per “Ariel”<lb/>I am now
                acknowledging correct receipt of your esteemed letter from 23rd of the<lb/>same
                month and thank you for the prompt shipping of the rest of my goods from the
                “Parwan”.<lb/> 83 crates of beer<lb/> 1 crate of instruments<lb/>which I have
                correctly received by means of “Yangtze”. In line with your note<lb/>I am gratefully
                crediting you with <lb/> $ 1,084.25.<lb/>for various expenses and charges and have
                verified the listing in my <lb/>invoice with my balance of $2,569. _. in your
                favour, <lb/>which I will immediately take steps to cover. <lb/>Yours sincerely and
                respectfully <lb/>R. Gaertner.<lb/>P. S. <lb/>The same <lb/>is asking you kindly to
                forward the inserts.</p>
         <pb facs="1870_09_29_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_R_Gaertner_Hakodate_2.tif" n="2"/>
